<Content>Stunning Schiller The hotel is situated about 20 minute walk from the station in Rembrandtplein Square area. The reception is large and rustic. All the reception staff spoke excellent English and were extremely helpful. We arrived early but the room was not ready however, they more than happy to store our large luggage cases. There are several cafes and restaurants situated right around the corner from the hotel. The hotel was in a very central location with good tram links. Our room was a decent size by European hotel standards and contained a safe, hairdryer and a whole range of free toiletries e.g. brush, toothbrush, razor etc which were restocked everyday. The decor was very modern and the bed was extremely comfortable. We were situated at the front of the hotel and looked out directly onto the square. At night it could be a bit noisy due to the fact the windows didn't appear to be double glazed however, it didn't stop me from sleeping. Opposite our window was a massive tv screen attached to another building for advertising purposes and whilst it did not bother us flashing all day and night it may bother some. The curtains however managed to block out most of the flashing at night.Overall a very enjoyable stay! I would certainly go back or recommend this to anyone who is looking for a handy hotel as a base to explore the city. 
